manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Vacuum Cleaner Cordless - Experience the freedom of cordless cleaning as you move from room to room without the limitations of a power cord. No more tangling or searching for power outlets. Our wireless vacuum cleaner provides the flexibility you need to clean efficiently and effectively.

Extendable Vacuum Cleaners - The compact and lightweight design of our cordless vacuum cleaners allows you to reach every corner of your living space with ease. Whether you're cleaning floors, low-pile carpet, or hard-to-reach areas, its portability ensures effortless movement and free cleaning.

HEPA Filter - The High Efficiency Particulate Air filter is designed to capture smaller particles, including allergens, pollen, and fine dust. It removes up to 99.97% of particles as small as 0.3 microns, ensuring cleaner air and reducing the risk of allergies or respiratory issues.

Crevice Tool Attachment The specially designed gap tool is the perfect accessory for reaching tight spaces and narrow gaps to keyboard crevices and baseboard edges. Enhanced Visibility Equipped with four LED lights on the brush head, our vacuum cleaner illuminates dark corners and under furniture, leaving no dirt or dust unseen. Cleaning Brush Attachment The cleaning brush attachment is a versatile tool that enhances the functionality of our wireless vacuum cleaner. It effectively clean debris. Telescopic Tube Our vacuum cleaner comes with a retractable aluminum tube to make your cleaning more convenient. Whether clean up dust in high places or debris.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 26, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Awesome addition to my cleaning routine
reviews.reviewText: Integrating this cordless vacuum into our daily chaos of a dog, the little ones, and our sprawling place has genuinely simplified life. The battery is a real trooper, allowing me to navigate the mess even after an hour of use. The 5-layer filter does its job, tackling the daily dirt, though shaking it off can be a bit of a dusty shuffle. Suction power is solid - not a carpet superhero, but it gets the job done.Now, the telescopic tube and wall-friendly setup are absolute lifesavers in my home hustle. The flexible brush and LED lights might be a tad extra, but they add a bit of flair to the cleaning gig. In my house, you might find yourself emptying the dirt bin more often, but the no-fuss vibe totally balances it out. With a dog, kids, and a house that seems to grow messes overnight, this cordless vacuum is the hero that's making everyday chaos in my life feel much less stressful.Overall, I'm glad I bought this. Better than my old Dyson.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 22, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars I love this cordless vac.
reviews.reviewText: This is my first cordless vac, and I have bought to use in my kitchen and family room. One has tiles and other has wooden floor. It works great on such floors. It is very light and is quite to work with. In fact I enjoy using this cordless vac. I am also cleaning my carpeted staircase using hand held with adapter supplied. It cleans well including dog hair. With other vacs the dog hair were difficult to clean but this one does the job. The battery life is decent too. I charge once a day to do my daily routine. Emptying the canister is easy. Even with low setting it cleans well. The adapters supplied help me to do small jobs like car cleaning, underneath sofa seats etc. I am happy with my purchase, and I strongly recommend it.

reviews.reviewText: Wasn't as nice as I'd hoped- minimal suction & power drains pretty quickly ...I will try recharging & update if any better .Acceptable, but barely, at this point...

I love this vacuum cleaner. It’s portable and powerful. Very good suction power. Picks up pet hair flawlessly. It is very handy. Battery life is good for me to vacuum small areas. It is good for everyday cleaning around the kitchen and other areas for a quick clean up. That is what I basically needed it for. Maneuverability is good, it can get into the hard to reach places with a big sized one. It’s a bonus that it can be used as handheld for cars.I have only used it on low so far. And even keeping it on low it picks up everything. The light at the front is very handy. I am able to see everything in the dark corners. I am satisfied with my purchase and would highly recommend it.

this is an amazing vacuum cleaner. surprised by the efficiency of the suction and so easy to use. I actually prefer it to my dyson in so many ways. it has an on button you don't have to keep pressing to keep it on like the dyson. it is lightweight yet powerful. it manoeuvers around corners and gets into tight spaces. it's easy to clean and holds a charge for at least a half hour. honestly a fantastic surprise for the price. even if you own a more expensive vac this little charmer is a must have as a secondary vac to keep upstairs or in your finished basement so you don't have to lug your vac up and down the stairs like I was before this purchase. its even great in the garage for use on the cars.

Great price and functionality!! Perfect for every day use, super light, maneuvers well, good suction (2 settings) love the light to see what your vacuuming, and you don’t have to hold down the power button like you do with a Dyson. Also comes with attachment to make it a hand held. Battery does not last long so I charge between every use.Highly recommend

reviews.reviewTitle: Not for real people. - only light cleaning/influencers
reviews.reviewText: Okay so, this vacuum is not HORRIBLE. But its not great. even on sale for 150$, I am returning it, because my 30$ vacuum I got at walmart in 2010 does a better job.I had high hopes for this vacuum, but it fell short. It has great maneuverability, and is light weight, but it sucks for suction, and barely picked up my dogs fur, and the dirt collection cup is so small, that what it does pick up, you have to empty the dang thing 4 times in 10 minutes.I did learn from this vacuum that I like the cordless, stick vacuum design and after this one didn't preform I found another option on sale at Canadian tire, and instantly went and picked it up at 75%off.I bought the new vacuum cleaner after I decided I would return this one (within 5 mintues), I had JUST vacuumed with this one, and the new one (Bissel IconPet) filled up with fur in literally 5 seconds on an area rug I had just done- and my dog wasn't even home to re-fill the rug with fur.Long story short- I think if you were doing extremely light cleaning, and using this as a quick clean up- it would be fine-ish - albeit rather expensive for what it does. If you actually are a human being and have messes- (ie bungalow, no mudroom, a husband in trades, kids and pet(s), cook a lot, etc) then I highly recommend avoiding purchasing this vacuum even though it seems like a great deal. TBH I am pretty sure the original price is a scam since there is no way that this is a 600$+ vacuum. As I said, my 30$ option from 2010 has more suction.Update: I got a letter in the mail from the company saying for a 5-star review, they would send me a 40$ Amazon gift card. So to be clear that is a 669.00 vacuum, supposedly on sale for 199.00 with 50$ off on top of that, and they can still send a 40$ gift card to people... A tad bit suspicious

The media could not be loaded. I love that it looks exactly like the big fancy Dy*** brand without the price tag. It has powerful suction and 2 attachments included. It has 2 levels and both do a very good job. Carpet, tiles and hard wood floors were all cleaned very well. I love that the canister and filter is very simple and the hair and my cat's fur does not get tangled somehwere along the way and cleans off very easily. I would definitely recommend you buy this one specifically if you're in the market for a new cordless vaccuum.
